,Recommended,252630,7789408,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,Malev Da Shinobi,"Wow. This games simple appearance doesn't accurately express it's charm and atmosphere. This game is immersive beyond most modern titles, the sounds and the sound track for each level are diverse and unsettling in every sense.You might feel that the game is easy off the bat, and in some ways, the game is easy - it's not the difficulty of the enemies that provides all of the challenge here.But the game falls back on players making the errors, in some ways, klling themselves due to lax in mindset, or not paying attention and falling prey to the games many traps. The environment is what is deadly,  and when coupled with the certain abilities of the enemies.. even more so.Risk/Reward is built in to almost every aspect. As the currency in the game, Artifacts- is the same thing that you use to cast spells. Making every action when low on health and artifacts incredibly on edge, and can lead to a very intense playthrough where pressing escape to take a breath is a advocated practice.I've not managed to beat the game, but I've gotten pretty far.The game offers 3 diverse, Lovecraftian based worlds, with enemies correlating to the particular demi-god of that world. A hub world, which is very cool- and 1 special world in which I've not managed to beat.All of which are procedurally(randomlly??) generated, which makes the levels seem very maze like, yet fresh and exciting- with twist and turns, ups and downs that can leave you feeling lost and desperate.Be careful though, 1 mistake and death can cost you your entire run. Caution is of the upmost importance.The lore of this game is sparse, but told in a simple straightforward way that works with your imagination, over blasting you with cinematics, or long explanations.It's worth mentioning, that I've delved into lovecraftian fiction works almost exclusively because of this game, just to learn more of the names of these gods, and to try and figure out these odd creatures I'm encountering.I've left out a lot of things from my words here.. because they are worth finding out for yourself.Don't skip out on this unique experience, for it's current price, and even full price. It's worth it."
