76561198025093178,Recommended,252630,11812063,"Posted: 21 August, 2014",all,ihKu47,"A fun rogue-like stealth title you can pick up and play for a few minutes at a time (game saves on exit), or be drawn in for significant periods of time - even if you initially intended to play just for a bit. The enemies may look all cute and cuddly but don't be fooled: after the first temple you're up against some mean SOB's and you have to either get good at dodging or really make use of your stealth skills. The difference in difficulty actually works in the game's favour for me; I can use the first temple to go and stab a few fish men when I want to just refresh in the middle of the day and get an actual challenge from the later levels.In addition to stabbing, shooting enemies you will get to make use of the powers of the Elder Gods, like hypnosis, and there will even be special weapons up ahead after the first temple. I won't spoil them for you, however. The strength of the game isn't in the gadgets though, but in the nicely polished gameplay that balances between sneaking, paying attention to your environment, looting and making a run for it when you find yourself in a sticky situation.If you enjoy stealth and want a title you can pick-and-play whenever you wish Eldritch is well worth the full 12€ price, and if it's on sale it's an absolute steal!"
