76561197979851880,Recommended,252630,7822342,"Posted: 29 November, 2013",all,Doubtful,"Think ""♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ child of Dishonored and HP Lovecraft"" in the form of a lightweight stealth/action/horror game with roguelike elements such as permadeath and procedurally generated voxel-based levels.*Also, please don't judge the game by the tone of the preview video's energy and music.  It does not capture the feel of playing this game in the least.  Watch a video on youtube before making up your mind.  This game is generally slow-paced, a bit creepy, and involves a lot of meticulous exploration.Despite having roguelike elements and a more oldschool-gaming attitude, it's not terribly difficult if you're experienced at stealth games.  Hell of a lot of fun, creepy and unsettling, and each run will challenge you about the same as the last due to the random terrain/maze-like levels.  Do not be fooled by the ease of clearing the first world; the second world is by far the most hazardous!Simple gameplay with several ways to fight, a stealth system including the ability to ""lose"" a pursuer, and a ""sneak attack"" system for bonus damage.No cumbersome inventory management; simplified equipment system with a few upgrade slots, and a slot for 1 power/spell that can be changed easily.  High jump boots, lockpicking kits, magical amulet/token, etc.Voxel-based procedural world with nice atmospheric sound, music, and lighting.Great use of vertical space for levels overall and for each given floor, with lots of crawlspaces, hidey holes, ceilings, and cover to hide in. You can crawl, powerslide under low passages, sprint, or climb up ledges.You won't get hundreds of hours of gameplay out of this, but it's a great little game and has great potential if modders or the developers design additional levels to explore and enemies to fight.  And it stands on its own feet just fine."
