,Recommended,252630,7879169,"Posted: 2 December, 2013",all,Lightning Dust,"I've played for hours now and I still find it fun. I've completed these with 9 resurrects and countless Medical Kits revival. For spoiler reasons, there is an alternative ending.Once you have managed to finish a playthrough, there will be a orbm when you resurrect, for you to pick up to drastically increase the difficulty.Overall, this game has limitless replayability. The dungoens, items, and enemies are randomized every time you resurrect. All 4 dungoens has its own set of enemies and items. There are 3 levels per dungoen, and in each level there are 3 floors. Because of this, the game encourages the player to explore.The player has the ability to destroy and create blocks if they have visited the Destruction Amulet and the Materialisation Shrine. The player also have an option to use the dynamite to destroy walls and/or floors to create a new path. Eldritch also has some good stealth elements. It is up to the players to either go stealthy or just rush through the dungeons. But the more dungoen you enter, the more harder is it for you to escape without dying. Enemies will chase you until you are out of their sight for a few seconds.There is also a shopkeeper per level. Stealing, attemping to directly kill him or setting off the shopkeeper's dynamite, he will come after you. Shopkeepers are one of the most hardest to kill when the player enrages them.Albeit the game's lack of content, the equipable items and magic are enough to satisfy multiple aspects of Eldritch."
