,Recommended,252630,7478069,"Posted: 25 October, 2013",all,GameDragonZero,"An interesting Rougelike mixing randomness and roguelikes, cartoony Lovecraftianism, and stealth/survival.  It's a simple but precise affair - explore three random dungeons to find artifacts and escape.  Only you have to do it in one go and each dungeon gets harder and weirder.  You can save some cash between levels for use when you die, but otherwise it's pretty hardcore.  Not perfect and a bit unpolished, but it delivers its challenge effectively and seems to be intended to be simple, straightfoward, and hard.  The sound effects and more-disturbing-over-time enemies are the most effective part of the game.  I'm not sure on the replayability and if every gamer is willing to make so many endurance runs over and over, so I can't give it a complete thumbs up.  However it's precise, effective delivery is praiseworthy and it can be strangely compelling if you're the kind of person who likes learning from defeat."
