,Recommended,252630,21083193,"Posted: 9 February, 2016",all,「Mentle」ゴ,"A fine example of roguelike(lite?) done right. This game has, at first glance, mucky graphics, but do fit well with everything that happens within the actual game. It has dungeon crawler written all over it, and the HP Lovecraft feel/inspiration is enough to grasp fans and unfamiliars alike. The game has solid gameplay, basic controls with very little to learn. It's forgiving at times, and unforgiving the next. It has a very nice simplistic feel to it with a bit of story tacked on, but not in a bad way. If you want it solely because you want a decent roguelike, pick it up. If you like HP Lovecraft, pick it up. If you want a decent mystery/horror game, pick it up.Overall?: 8/10.It will keep you gripped for a long while to come, and it's easily addictive. Being the roguelike it cherishes itself to be, it will be able to have some high replayability. There is a bit of a learning curve to overcome, but nothing too threatening."
