,Not Recommended,252630,32705157,Posted: 23 June,all,C-zom,"This will be one of my shorter reviews than usual. Maybe even my shortest, as there is only so much to say.As a short little adventure title for pennies on sale most of the time, Eldritch is cool. It has an interesting depth to the levels and enough equipment and spells to keep you amused. But I suppose I'll be the first one on these reviews to address the elephant in the room; how the hell are Lovecraft fans supposed to enjoy this? This is just like Cthulhu Saves the World.Seeing Lovecraft and his vision for a horrorifying, pessimistic, hopeless universe in multimedia can occasionally be rewarding but is ultimately frustrating. His writing is cumbersome, the themes are heavier than the books they're in, his characters are two dimensional and his racism is profound. But within that mire of faults and error is a diamond; his ability to invoke fear, ask horrible questions with awful answers, and question our place in the cosmos. He does this by using his literary tropes similar to how one uses magnifying glasses on ants.And then there are the monsters. The Elder Gods. The Old Ones. The interesting but underdeveloped worldbuilding exposition he used to cover his laymans knowledge of the occult, to plug in the gaps where ghouls and ghosts would wander in the Gothics of old. And the mainstream has latched onto these beings like a cancer and love to tout the tentacled plushies, trinkets, and alphabet network TV show references to them while completely foresaking both their intention and source.Eldritch does this in spades.2/5: Worth it on sale for voxel adventure fans. Lovecraft fans in hopes for an homage, beware.Pros:*Colorful, cute, interesting graphics with a fun take on voxel exploration/indie games.*Sound design is great. Loved the music, too.*Hilariously short. A little replayable. Some decent equipment/item/combat choices.Cons:*As Lovecraftian as Cthulhu Saves the World.*Totally devoid of atmosphere or story.*Tends to take long jabs at the fanbase, source material, and embellishes its black sarcasm towards these too much.*Meaningless procedural generation because there are only three biomes max.*Combat is no more complex than Terraria or Minecraft, maybe even simpler."
