76561198014229134,Recommended,252630,8679705,"Posted: 12 January, 2014",all,Dorok,"It's a great unique stealth fps with levels like you have never seen before.Don't buy it for those reasons:- It's only a light Roguelike, ie the difficulty isn't high, the randomization is just fair, don't buy it for this aspect.- It uses Lovecraft lore as thematic and there's some parts with a nice mood plus some interesting implementation of some monsters, but don't look for a Lovecraft game.But you could buy it for those reasons:- It is very fun from the fps stealth point of view, the stealth gameplay is quite intuitive and feels more natural than usual.- It has huge large levels with an extreme exploitation of heights as almost no fps made use at this level, one exception I know is the old fps Po'ed. That levels design would be enough to justify the use of sample graphics, to allow such large and complex levels inside descent production cost.- The levels have a fair randomization, but they have also an accurate tuned design for the exploration and progression point of view.- It offers a good range of tools to manage the levels in different ways.- Some monsters are quite unique, without to spoil anything, one really worth the quote, some statues you really need experiment in the game.Overall it's a game aimed to be relatively short but quite intense. The rogue-like aspect uses the fair randomization and helps increase the duration. It's a light fps stealth game with unique large levels exploiting intensively the heights, some parts succeed generate a rather good mood despite the low budget on graphics and sounds."
