,Recommended,252630,19326769,"Posted: 27 November, 2015",all,Future Ivy,"A fantastic rouge-like styled after the classic horror novels by H.P. Lovecraft with difficulty only matched by its tense atmosphere and wonderful diversity in each play. It's by no means simple and you most certainly won't complete it in your first ten, twenty, fifty attempts! Heck, even with a huge statement like that I've only put a hearty 12+ hours into it so it's most certainly ""learnable."" It all relies on how quickly you can gracefully adapt to the game's changing environments... And I do mean gracefully. After mastering the game's controls (running, jumping, sliding, leaping and all that will be used quite frequently) you almost feel like you're being thrown around the map! On top of that you have a simple but hardly repetitive group of enemies to deal with ranging from fish-men to flying... organs? It's easy to conclude ""well this is just impossible"" but the game actually does have quite a few ways to completing it! Throwing yourself into the storm over and over won't do you much good so it's always good to take on a strategy. I've recently found stealthiness to be the ultimate path but you do have to be ready to lose some 35-50 minutes instantly from simple mistakes. If you don't feel like taking on all ""three"" worlds at once (it's difficult beyond comprehension but I've done it multiple times!) you can also try the Mountains of Madness: 10 levels ofpure hellto retrieve your plane keys (keeping close to the books as always) and then heading all 10 levels back up to the surface! Fun alternative, right? Except.... Well, It's super tense and you'll get lost more than once as it begins to feel more like a labyrinth.SPOILERS/TIPSA great way to start any campaign is by grabbing the compass from Dagon [The first world ] and returning to The Library. Next you'll probably want to do the Trick or Treat world [ the pumpkin in the bar area ] be prepared to spend about 2-5 minutes here gathering materials for your next run! After you've grabbed a grappling hook and a gun with over 15+ ammo, return to The Library and re-enter Dagon. Complete the first world as so:[for beginners]:-Always look for a way down and try not to re-enter previously entered rooms-Avoid looting dead bodies... and don't waste ammo on those that don't need to be killed!-Press Z to throw items (great if you need to drop your gun/grappling hook for a takeout punch)-Hold spacebar to lift yourself over ledges! It took me almost 8 hours to realize this... it'll save you keys and such, allow you into new rooms, and save you from getting stuck in holes-run and press C (the crouch button for sneaking) to do a power-slide! You'll look cool AND it'll make your jumps longer![For returning players]-Approach levels slowly! Pay attention to the map! Knowing your surroundings is almost necessary to escaping any level-If the opportunity to rush through a floor is available then you should most certainly take it; especially in later levels where there are tons of baddies chasing you down-don't hug walls unless you're sneaking; enemies can easily get the jump on you-try not to forget to peek around corners if you're uncertain how safe a room is (C+E/Q). You can shoot and cast spells when you're in this position-It took me nearly 70 attempts to complete the game and I have no doubt it'll take plenty less for you. Keep at it, soldier!"
