76561198035945698,Recommended,252630,16559469,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,UnlosingJohn,"Eldritch is as cool as it sounds. It's fun, well-designed, surprisingly atmospheric, and even a bit terrifying at times (there's at least one enemy that will keep you extremely paranoid).My favorite part about the game is the 3D design of the levels. Each floor has multiple ""sub-floors"" and there are a lot of ways to move between sub-floors. Finding the exit is usually not too difficult, but finding your way to a shop or other area of interest can be surprisingly involved. There are also ways to get around this such as dynamite and pickaxes, which really take advantage of the 3D maze design.While the game itself is a bit short, it can take a good number of attempts to complete it, not counting the extra campaign that can be accessed right from the start. Survival means learning the hazards of each area and how each enemy behaves. There's a lot of challenge to this game, but it ultimately feels fair.There's also a decent amount of extra stuff to go for when you beat the game, such as a harder new game+ mode, a super-tough extra area with a leaderboard, some challenging achievements, and more.As someone who was just getting tired of roguelikes, this game was refreshing and fun."
