76561198019216815,Recommended,252630,30760247,Posted: 26 March,all,Crebmen,"Eldritch is a first-person, rogue-lite, action-horror game in which you delve deeper into various dungeons while combating the *eldritch* beings that reside within them.The game's horror elements are what set it apart from other rogue-lites. I was constantly on my toes, taking the game at a slow pace, trying to plan around what monsters I would face on floors below.However, as my play-time grew longer and I gained more experience with the game mechanics, Eldritch's horror-elements began to peel away as I understood how easy the game actually was. Keep up a brisk pace, know which enemies to take out first, collect a strong enough arsenal, and the game becomes a lot less interesting than it was during your first play-through.As such, I don't think Eldritch is a rogue-lite that begs to be played over and over like its contemporaries (there aren't really any unlocks either so it doesn't reward multiple playthroughs anyways). It's incredibly simple and effective, a rogue-lite that doesn't ask for much of your time, and that's what makes Eldritch recommendable.PROS:- Simple yet charming graphics.- Strongly atmospheric SFX and ambience.- Fun and interesting gameplay mechanics.- Great gameplay progression.CONS:- Very little replay value.- Loses its horror elements as you learn the mechanics.SCORE: 8/10"
76561198105261460,Recommended,252630,20998080,"Posted: 6 February, 2016",all,Pa4o_StaN | UnOfficial .✓,"Eldritch ✓Thoughts On The GameA fun and difficult, first-person, rogue-like game. The pixelated graphics add more beauty into the game. At first you will think it's all for laughs and enjoyment and it is, but after 4 hours of playing, you will think differently. The terror that get to you that you will lose all your progress (perma death) when you get really deep in this world really gets you on edge. You'll try to sneak past enemies, make tough decisions which weapons to drop and which to keep. Should you keep exploring for something better or are you better just running to the exit? What will you face later into Eldritch? It's your way.But What Is This Game About ?You select how your character looks like. You are spawned into a library, with 4 books that lead you to the levels you want. Each book has 3 or 4 levels and when you get to the end, before exiting a book, you get an orb, this orb must go onto a pedestal at the library. After collecting all 3 orbs from the 3 books, they all must go onto their places in front of a door (which is again, in the library). After that you go through the door, complete another 3 or 4 levels. but this time, instead of going down to the exit, like in the other books, this time you must go upwards to the exit. through ladders and enemies. If this isn't enough for you. There are 3 bonus levels, which 2 lead you to a level that you need to compete with other players to get a high score and 1 is a pumpkin that lets get items that you might need, while running away from creatures.What Do You Think About The Ending ?Honestlydisappointing. After all the intense stuff from the game, you just get a little text for what you have done (stats) and then it cuts to credits. I don't know what more i want. Maybe a little cut-scene ? How you get out of that library or something maybe ? I don't knowAnd After All This ?Great game. Enjoyed it for a long while. Absolutely recommend ✔"
