76561198130948719,Recommended,252630,34495297,Posted: 25 August,all,Gamboleer,"HARDWARE: Windows 10 x64, i5 3570. GTX 1070. No slowdowns or crashes.I saw this for $1 at a favorite bundle site and remembered I had it in my library, so I loaded it up. I'm a sucker for pixel-style graphics.It's definitely a rogue-like, and more of a first-person stealth game than a shooter. There aren't many enemies, but the ones you encounter can put a swift end to you, as you can take exactly 3 hits before it's game over, and some of your enemies fight at range. You also find limited ammo for the ranged weapons you can acquire, which means much of your combat will be hand-to-hand, and better done by attacking from behind, before you're detected.The music and sound effects are creepy and the overall aesthetic is effective at keeping you feeling slightly on edge as you travel through the levels.I enjoyed the ability to use my pistol as a retrievable throwing weapon once I ran out of bullets. Other common weapons are daggers for hand-to-hand, stones for throwing, and I even found the occasional bundle of dynamite, which I probably needed to use against the giant slime that ended my first play session. I put all 7 rounds of ammunition into that sucker and stabbed it a few times, but it still killed me."
